# LLM-Powered CAM Report Generation via docxtpl

Replace the current `python-docx` text-dump approach with a professional **LLM + Word Template** pipeline. The CAM agent will send the full UCSO to the Groq LLM, receive a structured JSON with all 85+ tags, and render them into the professionally designed `trinetra_cam_template.docx`.

---

## Root Cause

The current `cam-agent/main.py` uses 300+ lines of manual `doc.add_paragraph()` and `doc.add_table()` calls that produce an ugly, unformatted document. It cannot produce executive summaries, business analysis, or any qualitative content.

**After this fix:**
```
UCSO (all 13 agents) → Groq LLM → Structured JSON (85+ fields) → docxtpl → Beautiful .docx
```

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **New dependency**: `docxtpl` (pure Python, no system deps). Will be added to `agents/requirements.txt`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Groq API usage**: Each CAM generation will make **1 Groq API call** (~4000 tokens). This is within free-tier limits.

> [!WARNING]
> **Template file location**: The template `trinetra_cam_template.docx` must be placed at `agents/cam-agent/trinetra_cam_template.docx`. This file will be copied from the project root during setup.

